    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-10T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="220"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1178.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-10T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Is amount Santo Domingo owes Banco Nacional included in first amount mentioned in
                    your January 5, 11 a.m.?</p>
                <p>Have salaries October to January been paid? If not, telegraph their approximate
                    total.</p>
                <p>What practical assurances can Santo Domingo, if relieved of its present financial
                    difficulties, give that it will thereafter live within its net income?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
